<plot>It is the year of 1953 in the village of San Jacinto, Colombia. Dolores Salinas is a 60 year old woman who makes her living out of praying at funerals. Usually the dead people have been left by the Colombian political war period, who fought in the lines of the conservative party. Now the body of her son arrives, who was killed during this war but fighting for the ideals of the liberal party (the opposite side), and she will have to find a place to bury him.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?154676</url></doc>
